    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** serving as our clear focal point. At a 75.32 efficiency score, his matchup against Leiter is bolstered not only by a favorable SP xERA of 4.43 but specifically by the high-probability environment for stolen bases; with a slow opposing pitcher delivery and the 5-hole protection, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** is the primary engine for our scarcity-weighted strategy. **Josh Naylor** (68.39) and **Seiya Suzuki** (66.18) provide high-floor stability, both benefiting from soft matchups against Prielipp and V\u00e1squez, respectively. **Seiya Suzuki** in particular sees his value elevated by a +19% bump due to the opposing pitcher\u2019s inefficiency, making him a cornerstone of today's scoring projection.\n\nThe most critical bench decision involved balancing the marginal utility of **Trevor Story** (55.32) against our depth. While **Trevor Story** earned the start due to his ability to exploit a slow delivery for stolen base upside, he narrowly edged out the rest of the bench\u2014though it must be noted that our elite speed options like **Corbin Carroll**, **James Wood**, **Mickey Moniak**, and **Brice Turang** are unavailable today due to team off-days. We remain cautious regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Dalton Rushing**, **Alex Freeland**, **Jose Caballero**, and **Giancarlo Stanton**; should these players be shifted down in their respective batting orders by their managers, their already precarious efficiency scores could dip into sub-40 territory, triggering a potential benching to protect our game caps. We are also closely monitoring the weather, as the \"Wind Out\" factor is providing a modest boost to **Dalton Rushing** and **Alex Freeland**, which currently keeps them viable despite their lower spots in the order.",
